      "message": "I think so, but I wouldn\u0027t risk it.  I think we\u0027re pushing our luck with methods like makePoint() and makeMatrix() as-is.  If they need to exist, we really should void make_foo(T*) them like we\u0027ve done everywhere else.  I\u0027d say makePoint() probably doesn\u0027t need to exist:\n\nSkPoint pts[2];\nfuzz-\u003enext(\u0026pts[0].fX, \u0026pts[0].fY, \u0026pts[1].fX, \u0026pts[1].fY);\n\nAnother handy thing we might add to make this easier is\n\ntemplate \u003ctypename T\u003e\nvoid nextN(T* ptr, int n) {\n   for (int i \u003d 0; i \u003c n; i++) {\n       this-\u003enext(ptr+i);\n   }\n}\n\nThat could make makePoint() and makeMatrix() really moot:\n\nSkPoint pt;\nthis-\u003enextN(\u0026pt.fX, 2);\n\nSkScalar mat[9];\nthis-\u003enextN(mat, 9);\nSkMatrx m;\nm.set9(mat);",
